.TH TTSD 1 "March 2025" "Dawnstar ReadAloud 1.1.0" "System Daemon"
.SH NAME
ttsd \- Text-to-Speech daemon for low-latency speech synthesis
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ttsd
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ttsd
is a background daemon that provides low-latency text-to-speech synthesis.
By running as a persistent process, it eliminates the startup overhead of
loading TTS engines, making speech synthesis nearly instantaneous.

The daemon communicates via a Unix socket and can be controlled using the
.B ttsc
client application.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-lang\fR=\fILANG\fR
Default language code (default: en-us)
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-speed\fR=\fISPEED\fR
Default speech speed: slow, normal, fast (default: normal)
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Enable verbose logging
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-cache\fR
Disable audio caching
.TP
\fB\-\-socket\fR=\fIPATH\fR
Unix socket path (default: $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/tts-daemon.sock)
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-daemon\fR
Run as background daemon (fork to background)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show help message
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
SIGTERM, SIGINT
Gracefully shutdown the daemon
.SH SYSTEMD INTEGRATION
The daemon can be run as a systemd user service:
.EX
systemctl --user enable tts-daemon
systemctl --user start tts-daemon
.EE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/tts-daemon.sock
Unix socket for IPC
.TP
.I ~/.cache/tts_app/
Audio cache directory
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Start daemon in foreground:
ttsd
.TP
Start daemon with verbose logging:
ttsd -v
.TP
Start daemon in background:
ttsd --daemon
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tts (1),
.BR ttsc (1)
